Queensland Fire &
Emergency Services (QFES) crews remain on scene at a grass fire burning in a
north-easterly direction towards Old Toweran Road, Lowmead. The slow moving
fire which broke out on Saturday is under control and posing no threat to
property at this time. Fire crews are undertaking backburning operations and
will continue to patrol the fire over the coming days. Nearby residents may be
affected by a smoke haze for the rest of today and overnight. Residents are
asked to close windows and doors and if suffering from a respiratory condition,
keep medications close by. Motorists should drive with caution and to
conditions. If residents are concerned their property is under threat, they are
advised to call Triple Zero (000) immediately.

properties.description:
Gillies Range, Little Mulgrave– grass fire as at 4.25pm Sat 4 October  
Queensland Fire and Emergency Services (QFES) advises there is a grass fire burning in inaccessible land at the bottom of the Gillies Range, Little Mulgrave. The fire has been contained however thick smoke is being pushed towards Gordonvale and may also be visible to motorists and residents in the vicinity of Gillies Range Road and Roos Road. The fire is posing no threat to property at this time. Residents are asked to close windows and doors and if suffering from a respiratory condition, keep medications close by. Motorists should drive with caution and to conditions. If residents are concerned their property is under threat, they are advised to call Triple Zero (000) immediately.

Cooktown – vegetation fire as 5.10pm Sun 4 October
Queensland Fire and Emergency Services (QFES) crews advises there is a vegetation fire in Cooktown. The fire is burning in the vicinity of Ironwood Avenue, Oaky Creek Road, Percy Road and surrounding streets including Poison Creek Road, Solander Road, Lee Road and Flaggy Road. The fire is posing no threat to property at this time. Firefighters are strengthening containment lines with aerial support and will monitor it overnight. Nearby residents may be affected by smoke. Residents are asked to close windows and doors and if suffering from a respiratory condition, keep medications close by. Motorists should drive with caution and to conditions. If residents are concerned their property is under threat, they are advised to call Triple Zero (000) immediately.
